tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and high chloride. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible renal dysfunction and metabolic derangement. HbA1c is low despite glucosuria, which may reflect recent glycemic changes or analytical issues. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, assessment for possible diabetes or metabolic disorder, and clinical correlation.
